00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,580
This series is crafted for the purpose of entertainment.

2
00:00:02,580 --> 00:00:04,820
All characters, behaviours, settings, and events depicted in this drama are entirely fictitious.

3
00:00:04,820 --> 00:00:06,660
They are not designed to allude to any particular entity, occupation, or group of people.

4
00:00:06,660 --> 00:00:09,980
Viewer discretion is advised.

5
00:00:10,020 --> 00:00:12,620
[North Star Entertainment]

6
00:00:26,180 --> 00:00:32,220
♫I never know what love is like♫

7
00:00:32,220 --> 00:00:37,020
♫All my life, never once have I experienced it♫

8
00:00:37,020 --> 00:00:40,340
♫No one to take that place in my heart♫

9
00:00:41,580 --> 00:00:47,580
♫But now that I’ve met you, my heart begins to glow♫

10
00:00:47,580 --> 00:00:52,340
♫What feeling is this? Why is my heart fluttering?♫

11
00:00:52,340 --> 00:00:56,460
♫And I just can’t control it.♫

12
00:00:56,460 --> 00:01:00,300
♫What happened to my heart right now?♫

13
00:01:00,300 --> 00:01:04,140
♫I can’t control it when you’re around♫

14
00:01:04,140 --> 00:01:10,300
♫This heart…it stops at you♫

15
00:01:11,140 --> 00:01:15,340
♫ Is this love? Is that what they call it?♫

16
00:01:15,340 --> 00:01:18,740
♫ When my heart starts to waver♫

17
00:01:18,740 --> 00:01:23,380
♫ Like a stream of water slowly pouring over my heart♫

18
00:01:23,380 --> 00:01:26,460
♫ From dusk till dawn, you’re never far from my sight♫

19
00:01:26,460 --> 00:01:30,860
♫ Or is this love? Are you that someone...♫

20
00:01:30,860 --> 00:01:34,340
♫ ...who’s destined to be with me?♫

21
00:01:34,340 --> 00:01:40,500
♫ Is this really happening ? I really want to know ♫

22
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:41,740
♫‘Cos you now hold a special place in my heart♫

23
00:01:41,740 --> 00:01:46,420
[Waves of Deception]
♫‘Cos you now hold a special place in my heart♫

24
00:01:47,360 --> 00:01:49,660
[Previously]
You and Boss came out of,

25
00:01:49,660 --> 00:01:51,340
that room after three in the morning.

26
00:01:51,460 --> 00:01:53,500
It’s just a rumour. Don’t mind it.

27
00:01:53,600 --> 00:01:56,340
But people don’t usually forget this kind of rumour, Boss.

28
00:01:56,530 --> 00:01:58,130
Papa’s here to see you, Chonlada.

29
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:00,180
- Papa?!
- Papa?!

30
00:02:00,180 --> 00:02:01,820
Why are you taking my staff out here?

31
00:02:02,300 --> 00:02:04,900
I just want to get to know the person you’re dating.

32
00:02:04,960 --> 00:02:06,940
If you refuse to talk nicely,

33
00:02:06,940 --> 00:02:09,660
have fun living with the rumour then.

34
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:13,260
Miss Preem, do you want an assistant?

35
00:02:13,730 --> 00:02:15,060
Hey, look out!

36
00:02:15,100 --> 00:02:16,340
I’m so sorry.

37
00:02:16,340 --> 00:02:17,500
Are you all right, Miss Apo?

38
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:19,760
Why didn’t you tell your brother about Chef Ian?

39
00:02:19,900 --> 00:02:22,980
Because Boss didn’t use the dirty way to get Chef Ian to work with her.

40
00:02:23,300 --> 00:02:24,420
Take some pills too.

41
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:26,060
I’m not worried about you.

42
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:27,620
I’m more worried about myself.

43
00:02:39,860 --> 00:02:40,800
Miss Preem.

44
00:02:42,760 --> 00:02:44,700
I made an appointment with the doctor for you.

45
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:51,820
- But…
- I know Boss has asked you to take charge for her today.

46
00:02:52,200 --> 00:02:55,340
But if she knew you came to work while being sick,

47
00:02:55,700 --> 00:02:57,420
do you think she’d approve of that?

48
00:02:59,360 --> 00:02:59,940
Well, I…

49
00:02:59,940 --> 00:03:02,540
What if she got a cold from you?

50
00:03:03,060 --> 00:03:05,740
Brrr, I don’t even want to think about it.

51
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:09,940
A workaholic who can’t work because she’s sick, can you imagine that?

52
00:03:12,160 --> 00:03:14,060
I’m getting goosebumps just by thinking of it.

53
00:03:19,460 --> 00:03:22,579
Okay, fine. But promise me,

54
00:03:22,760 --> 00:03:26,660
you’ll call me immediately if there’s any problem.

55
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:28,100
Absolutely.

56
00:03:34,060 --> 00:03:37,420
Can you put those documents in the folder for me then?

57
00:03:37,760 --> 00:03:40,730
Of course. Please get well soon.

58
00:03:55,600 --> 00:04:00,460
What?! Are you serious? Aren’t you afraid you’ll get caught?

59
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:02,860
Geez, why do you have to make a fuss?

60
00:04:03,060 --> 00:04:05,500
I’m only filling in for Miss Preem.

61
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:07,620
So, I’m just checking out other reports too.

62
00:04:07,660 --> 00:04:09,100
I haven’t done anything wrong yet.

63
00:04:09,380 --> 00:04:11,980
Will you swear it’s only about work?

64
00:04:12,460 --> 00:04:15,500
I know you’re sniffing around for top-secret information.

65
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:19,180
And you said you’d do it fair and square, huh?

66
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:23,940
I’m doing it. I’m checking whether the Watin Group is playing any dirty tricks.

67
00:04:24,260 --> 00:04:27,380
Because if they aren’t, then I’d be able to tell my brother that.

68
00:04:27,660 --> 00:04:32,180
Or you’re probably doing it to give yourself an excuse…

69
00:04:32,180 --> 00:04:34,700
for not telling your brother about Chef Ian…

70
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:41,380
because your boss didn’t do anything wrong, and because you’re falling into your own trap.

71
00:04:43,330 --> 00:04:47,500
You bonkers. Next time, try watching murder series too.

72
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:50,220
Don’t just watch romantic series that only keep you in the lavender field.

73
00:04:52,659 --> 00:04:54,980
Fine. Don’t say I didn’t warn you.

74
00:04:54,980 --> 00:04:57,820
If your dad knows that you’re disguising yourself,

75
00:04:57,820 --> 00:05:02,260
among the Watin Group. he’ll definitely eat you alive.

76
00:05:03,760 --> 00:05:08,300
Not to mention if you also happen to fall for Miss Apo.

77
00:05:10,530 --> 00:05:14,700
If he finds out about that? Brrr!

78
00:05:24,130 --> 00:05:30,180
Hello? Hello? Are you still there, Lada?

79
00:05:53,100 --> 00:05:54,500
What are you doing?

80
00:05:58,900 --> 00:06:01,340
What about you, Boss?  Why are you here?

81
00:06:01,340 --> 00:06:02,780
Or are you worried…

82
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:03,730
I’m not worried about anyone.

83
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:10,940
That’s not what I meant. I mean, are you worried about work?

84
00:06:11,860 --> 00:06:14,020
Or are you worried about Miss Preem?

85
00:06:14,730 --> 00:06:17,130
She’s gone to see the doctor since early morning.

86
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:21,700
Hasn’t she informed you?

87
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:25,260
Have you finished doing Miss Preem’s job?

88
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:30,180
If so, bring it to me. I need to check it first.

89
00:06:32,659 --> 00:06:33,900
Yes, Boss.

90
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:48,020
That was close.

91
00:07:07,180 --> 00:07:08,540
[Door knocking]

92
00:07:25,330 --> 00:07:28,020
If you know I’m here to fill in for Miss Preem,

93
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:31,730
that means she already told you she’d gone to see the doctor.

94
00:07:33,130 --> 00:07:35,000
Then, why are you still here?

95
00:07:35,860 --> 00:07:40,860
If it were Miss Preem, I wouldn’t have come to check on it.

96
00:07:43,330 --> 00:07:45,940
I see, you’re here because of me.

97
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:46,780
No.

98
00:07:49,100 --> 00:07:51,780
It’s because I don’t trust you to do the job alone.

99
00:07:54,400 --> 00:07:56,060
Please don’t omit it.

100
00:07:56,760 --> 00:07:59,420
I don’t want to hear any nonsense rumour again.

101
00:08:01,700 --> 00:08:02,780
I’m sorry.

102
00:08:03,420 --> 00:08:08,620
I’ll take my leave then, so no one would see us alone together…

103
00:08:08,980 --> 00:08:11,180
and circulate the rumour again.

104
00:08:11,820 --> 00:08:13,220
Please excuse me.

105
00:08:15,340 --> 00:08:17,260
Wait, Chonlada.

106
00:08:22,060 --> 00:08:23,360
What is it, Boss?

107
00:08:24,060 --> 00:08:25,980
Wait until I’m done first.

108
00:08:28,060 --> 00:08:31,420
If there’s nothing to correct, you can go then.

109
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:33,299
Yes, Boss.

110
00:08:35,059 --> 00:08:36,580
Where do you want me to wait?

111
00:08:55,300 --> 00:08:59,300
[Phone ringing]

112
00:09:02,460 --> 00:09:03,660
Yes, Boss?

113
00:09:03,860 --> 00:09:07,660
I've checked your work. Overall, it's fine.

114
00:09:08,160 --> 00:09:11,330
If everything is good, can I go home now?

115
00:09:12,860 --> 00:09:15,460
Make sure the computer is switched off, then you can go home.

116
00:09:16,500 --> 00:09:17,460
Yes, Boss.

117
00:09:20,460 --> 00:09:21,980
Finally!

118
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:24,500
I'm outta here.

119
00:10:05,860 --> 00:10:07,580
[Door knocking]

120
00:10:07,930 --> 00:10:08,940
Who is it?

121
00:10:19,530 --> 00:10:20,330
It’s just…

122
00:10:21,300 --> 00:10:27,420
Miss Preem has asked me to give you this eye drops, in case your eyes might get dry.

123
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:30,700
Here.

124
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:38,060
Okay, you can go home now.

125
00:10:50,660 --> 00:10:51,980
Please allow me.

126
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:57,220
Don’t move.

127
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:01,140
What are you doing?

128
00:11:01,660 --> 00:11:03,380
I said stay still.

129
00:11:16,330 --> 00:11:17,700
Please let me.

130
00:11:22,730 --> 00:11:24,660
Please don’t be stubborn.

131
00:12:37,340 --> 00:12:39,700
[Phone ringing]

132
00:12:45,330 --> 00:12:46,740
Yes, Miss Preem?

133
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:50,500
Oh, Boss already checked it.

134
00:12:52,130 --> 00:12:53,530
Please don’t worry.

135
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:58,940
Yes. Please rest well. Goodbye.

136
00:13:03,460 --> 00:13:05,730
You…you can go now.

137
00:13:10,130 --> 00:13:12,300
Aren’t you scared, working alone so late like this?

138
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:16,780
What do you want?

139
00:13:17,960 --> 00:13:21,100
I just feel guilty for letting you work so hard alone.

140
00:13:21,780 --> 00:13:24,300
If there’s anything I could help, please let me know.

141
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:27,020
I’m always willing to help.

142
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:31,260
You can leave.

143
00:13:32,140 --> 00:13:37,500
It’s something I have to decide, not the secretary’s assistant.

144
00:13:39,530 --> 00:13:41,380
Please tell me first.

145
00:13:41,560 --> 00:13:43,740
If it’s beyond my ability to help,

146
00:13:43,860 --> 00:13:47,300
I promise I won’t get in the way.

147
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:56,020
I’m taking a look at Chef Ian’s signature dishes for our campaign opening.

148
00:13:56,730 --> 00:14:01,500
From what we had tried last time, these three are the most interesting.

149
00:14:02,260 --> 00:14:07,940
But you can pick only one menu to be our hotel’s signature dish, right?

150
00:14:19,500 --> 00:14:26,660
Hmm…in my opinion, these three are all delicious!

151
00:14:29,500 --> 00:14:34,100
I could tell. You almost ate the plate too.

152
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:41,900
But if I have to choose one,

153
00:14:44,460 --> 00:14:45,930
I’ll pick this.

154
00:14:48,500 --> 00:14:49,980
Isn’t it too simple?

155
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:55,620
Yes, that’s why it’s interesting.

156
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:59,660
After facing a busy and hectic life all day long,

157
00:15:00,360 --> 00:15:03,020
we still have to think about what to have for dinner.

158
00:15:04,260 --> 00:15:06,700
Why don’t we try something not complicated?

159
00:15:06,700 --> 00:15:08,740
Make an ordinary thing special.

160
00:15:09,180 --> 00:15:13,540
Make a lasting impression for our guests, so that they’d want to come back again.

161
00:15:14,740 --> 00:15:19,660
That’s my idea. What do you think?

162
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:27,260
But you can’t use your preference to make a decision about work.

163
00:15:28,930 --> 00:15:29,730
Well…

164
00:15:31,660 --> 00:15:33,360
I was only suggesting.

165
00:15:35,730 --> 00:15:39,100
What about you, Boss? Which one do you like?

166
00:15:46,360 --> 00:15:47,380
Not answering.

167
00:15:48,380 --> 00:15:51,180
Well then, I won’t bother you anymore.

168
00:15:51,860 --> 00:15:56,100
Have fun working alone, Boss. Good night!

169
00:16:13,130 --> 00:16:16,020
It’s late. I’d be surprised if I could get a cab at this hour.

170
00:16:34,600 --> 00:16:35,620
Get in the car.

171
00:16:36,500 --> 00:16:39,960
Don’t tell me you want me to go back and help you with your work.

172
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:53,940
Has Apo just let you out?

173
00:16:55,930 --> 00:16:58,140
Huh? How did you get here?

174
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:07,260
You can drop me off at the noodle shop near my place, Boss.

175
00:17:11,460 --> 00:17:13,900
Don’t tell me you’re craving for noodles at midnight.

176
00:17:16,060 --> 00:17:21,380
Well, I’ve worked so hard and used up a lot of energy.

177
00:17:21,380 --> 00:17:24,099
If I go back to my room now, I won’t be able to sleep because I’m hungry.

178
00:17:24,099 --> 00:17:27,300
Or maybe, do you want to join me?

179
00:17:28,099 --> 00:17:28,900
No.

180
00:17:30,530 --> 00:17:31,860
I thought so.

181
00:17:31,860 --> 00:17:35,220
You don’t even touch the food from your own hotel.

182
00:17:36,820 --> 00:17:39,460
You can stop over there.

183
00:17:57,360 --> 00:17:58,660
Thank you for driving me.

184
00:17:59,660 --> 00:18:00,660
It’s my way home.

185
00:18:18,360 --> 00:18:19,460
Are you ordering?

186
00:18:19,700 --> 00:18:20,740
Oh no, go ahead.

187
00:18:21,130 --> 00:18:23,860
Uncle, I’ll have a bowl of wonton soup please.

188
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:25,900
Sure. Please take a seat first.

189
00:18:45,560 --> 00:18:50,820
[What a close escape. If Boss had dropped me off at my place and bumped into Pat, I’d be so doomed!]

190
00:19:02,660 --> 00:19:03,820
Cover them.

191
00:19:08,660 --> 00:19:11,460
Boss? I thought you already left.

192
00:19:12,960 --> 00:19:13,930
Cover your legs.

193
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:33,180
It’s hot. Keep it for me first.

194
00:19:36,260 --> 00:19:37,580
What’s recommended here?

195
00:19:39,130 --> 00:19:40,060
Everything.

196
00:19:41,060 --> 00:19:43,660
What do you want to eat? I’ll order it for you.

197
00:19:44,620 --> 00:19:45,900
Anything is fine.

198
00:19:47,160 --> 00:19:51,020
Wow, that makes it a lot easier for me to decide.

199
00:19:52,860 --> 00:19:55,020
Excuse me? One more wonton soup please.

200
00:19:55,020 --> 00:19:56,700
Okay, sure.

201
00:20:01,930 --> 00:20:04,980
Why did you order that for me?

202
00:20:05,760 --> 00:20:08,130
Well, you don’t eat spicy food.

203
00:20:09,900 --> 00:20:11,260
Did Miss Preem tell you?

204
00:20:12,160 --> 00:20:14,460
No, I just know.

205
00:20:15,760 --> 00:20:16,540
How?

206
00:20:18,600 --> 00:20:20,740
That time when we went to Chef Ian’s restaurant,

207
00:20:20,740 --> 00:20:24,740
I noticed you always took a sip of water after every spicy dish.

208
00:20:24,740 --> 00:20:29,180
And your lips also turned redder and redder.

209
00:20:29,620 --> 00:20:32,900
That means you don’t like spicy food.

210
00:20:33,300 --> 00:20:36,460
So, wonton soup is the best choice for you.

211
00:20:38,700 --> 00:20:40,260
So, it’s just a coincidence.

212
00:20:41,730 --> 00:20:46,060
No, not a coincidence. It’s called “paying attention”.

213
00:20:46,420 --> 00:20:50,260
Just like this jacket you gave me to cover my legs.

214
00:20:50,620 --> 00:20:52,500
I know you’re not hungry.

215
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:56,540
You only sit with me because you want those men to stay away from me, don’t you?

216
00:21:07,800 --> 00:21:12,330
This kind of soup usually contains excessive amounts of sodium we need in a day.

217
00:21:13,400 --> 00:21:15,620
Be careful when you eat it.

218
00:21:17,730 --> 00:21:18,730
Are you worried about me?

219
00:21:20,930 --> 00:21:24,300
No. I’m only saying it because I’m your boss.

220
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:29,020
If anything happens to you, the hotel still has to pay for your welfare.

221
00:21:47,560 --> 00:21:48,780
Give me your arm, Boss.

222
00:22:19,460 --> 00:22:20,580
That arm too.

223
00:22:33,900 --> 00:22:38,340
I’m only doing this because I’m your secretary’s assistant.

224
00:22:38,800 --> 00:22:41,980
If your sleeves get caught and make the bowl drop,

225
00:22:42,160 --> 00:22:44,220
you might have to pay for our welfare then.

226
00:22:49,860 --> 00:22:52,160
You can go home after you finish eating.

227
00:22:56,800 --> 00:22:57,860
I’ll drop you home.

228
00:22:59,660 --> 00:23:03,420
That’s all right. It’s just around the corner. I can walk.

229
00:23:14,900 --> 00:23:20,460
You want to drop me off because you’re worried those men might do anything to me, don’t you?

230
00:23:24,960 --> 00:23:27,220
If so, that means you’re worried about me, Boss.

231
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:42,460
If I admit that I’m worried, will you let me drop you off?

232
00:23:49,500 --> 00:23:55,220
[♫I never know what love is like♫]

233
00:23:55,220 --> 00:24:00,140
[♫All my life, never once have I experienced it♫]

234
00:24:00,140 --> 00:24:03,500
[♫No one to take that place in my heart♫]

235
00:24:03,500 --> 00:24:05,660
If so, that means you’re worried about me.
[♫But now that I’ve met you, my heart begins to glow♫]

236
00:24:05,660 --> 00:24:07,500
[♫But now that I’ve met you, my heart begins to glow♫]

237
00:24:07,500 --> 00:24:10,820
If I admit I’m worried, will you let me drop you off?
[♫But now that I’ve met you, my heart begins to glow♫]

238
00:24:10,820 --> 00:24:15,620
[♫What feeling is this? Why is my heart fluttering?♫]

239
00:24:15,620 --> 00:24:19,500
[♫And I just can’t control it♫]

240
00:24:19,500 --> 00:24:23,580
♫What happened to my heart right now?♫

241
00:24:23,580 --> 00:24:27,060
♫I can’t control it when you’re around♫

242
00:24:27,060 --> 00:24:31,420
It’s not a coincidence. It’s called “paying attention”
[♫This heart…it stops at you♫]

243
00:24:33,960 --> 00:24:35,100
Give me your arm.
[♫ Is this love?♫]

244
00:24:35,100 --> 00:24:36,100
[♫ Is this love?♫]

245
00:24:36,100 --> 00:24:38,700
[♫Is that what they call it?♫]

246
00:24:38,700 --> 00:24:41,860
[♫ When my heart starts to waver♫]

247
00:24:41,860 --> 00:24:46,540
[♫ Like a stream of water slowly pouring over my heart♫]

248
00:24:46,540 --> 00:24:49,540
[♫From dusk till dawn, you’re never far from my thought♫]

249
00:24:49,540 --> 00:24:54,220
[♫Or is this love? Are you that someone...♫]

250
00:24:54,220 --> 00:24:57,620
[♫ ...who’s destined to be with me?♫]

251
00:24:57,620 --> 00:25:03,780
[♫ Is this really happening ? I really want to know ♫]

252
00:25:03,780 --> 00:25:08,060
[♫‘Cos you now hold a special place in my heart♫]

253
00:25:42,660 --> 00:25:46,020
If I admit I’m worried, will you let me drop you off

254
00:25:46,020 --> 00:25:50,860
Geez! Stop, stop, stop! Stop thinking! Stop thinking!

255
00:25:50,860 --> 00:25:52,540
Stop thinking about what?

256
00:25:55,360 --> 00:25:56,740
Huh, Miss Preem?

257
00:25:57,730 --> 00:25:59,780
Why don’t you take more days off?

258
00:26:00,560 --> 00:26:01,960
Why did you come to work?

259
00:26:02,760 --> 00:26:04,260
I’m feeling better now.

260
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:07,530
I feel so bad leaving you to do all the work alone yesterday.

261
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:12,500
Boss told me this morning that she has to attend a meeting with Big Boss.

262
00:26:12,660 --> 00:26:16,580
She might not come in until tomorrow. So, I’m here to take charge instead.

263
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:21,500
Ah, that’s why her room is so quiet.

264
00:26:21,530 --> 00:26:22,330
What?

265
00:26:23,760 --> 00:26:26,180
Do you have anything you want to talk to her?

266
00:26:27,200 --> 00:26:32,580
Well, yesterday Boss and I had some discussions about Chef Ian’s menu.

267
00:26:32,580 --> 00:26:37,740
So, I just want to know if she has already decided which menu would be the signature dish.

268
00:26:37,740 --> 00:26:41,100
Oh, that? Boss already talked to me about it last night.

269
00:26:41,100 --> 00:26:44,420
That’s why I’m here. I want to get it done as soon as I can.

270
00:26:47,130 --> 00:26:50,740
Can you tell me which menu she picked?

271
00:26:59,960 --> 00:27:01,660
Thinking of Lada?

272
00:27:04,660 --> 00:27:05,900
Dad.

273
00:27:06,460 --> 00:27:10,460
If that’s all you want to talk about, I’d rather get back to work.

274
00:27:11,160 --> 00:27:12,300
Hold on.

275
00:27:14,960 --> 00:27:19,900
Listen, Nam. I don’t have any debts.

276
00:27:19,900 --> 00:27:22,620
You don’t need to work so hard as if I had to pay off the debts.

277
00:27:25,100 --> 00:27:27,060
But we do have a rival, Dad.

278
00:27:27,060 --> 00:27:30,620
And since we recently beat the Wachara Group in the land auction,

279
00:27:30,620 --> 00:27:32,340
I don’t think Mr. Pheemdet would just sit there,

280
00:27:32,340 --> 00:27:35,500
and watch us rake in all the profits for our hotel and resort.

281
00:27:35,760 --> 00:27:40,460
I know. But life isn’t just about work, Nam.

282
00:27:43,930 --> 00:27:46,060
I don’t want you to end up like me.

283
00:27:47,960 --> 00:27:52,660
You know, by the time I realised how important that someone in my life was,

284
00:27:53,400 --> 00:27:55,100
I had lost all the chances to make her stay.

285
00:27:57,530 --> 00:28:02,100
Mum is now happy with her new family, Dad. Stop brooding about your past.

286
00:28:02,460 --> 00:28:06,700
I’m not brooding. I just want you to know…

287
00:28:06,700 --> 00:28:12,020
that if you have a chance to keep those you love and care close to you,

288
00:28:12,020 --> 00:28:13,500
don’t let that chance slip a...

289
00:28:13,500 --> 00:28:15,780
Chonlad is just a colleague, Dad.

290
00:28:16,060 --> 00:28:17,860
There’s nothing more than that.

291
00:28:20,260 --> 00:28:22,860
So, you don’t feel anything for her?

292
00:28:24,130 --> 00:28:28,400
Fine. Then, I won’t bother you with that again.

293
00:28:30,900 --> 00:28:36,140
Come to think of it, she also said the same thing that day. That she doesn’t like you.

294
00:28:39,060 --> 00:28:40,300
She said that?

295
00:28:43,260 --> 00:28:46,000
I actually didn’t want to talk to you about this.

296
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:48,660
It made me look immature.

297
00:28:49,360 --> 00:28:53,130
Maybe I should go talk to Lom and encourage her to go after Lada instead.

298
00:28:53,220 --> 00:28:54,140
You can’t.

299
00:28:54,930 --> 00:28:56,760
What rights do you have to stop me?

300
00:28:58,300 --> 00:29:01,580
You don’t understand. Chonlada is such a nuisance!

301
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:02,960
Nuisance? How?

302
00:29:04,130 --> 00:29:06,140
The more I think about it, it’s such a shame.

303
00:29:07,400 --> 00:29:12,780
I used to tell Lada that your biggest flaw is that you’re a workaholic.

304
00:29:13,620 --> 00:29:17,700
But she told me that’s not a flaw.

305
00:29:18,380 --> 00:29:24,780
The way she put it made me feel that she truly understands those who are obsessed with work.

306
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:29,180
Just like how your mother once understood me.

307
00:29:32,900 --> 00:29:35,500
Do you want Mum to have a fall-out with Daddy Andre or what?

308
00:29:38,500 --> 00:29:40,700
Fine, no more talking about the past.

309
00:29:41,660 --> 00:29:43,620
But I want you to remember this…

310
00:29:44,460 --> 00:29:46,700
You mightn’t believe me now.

311
00:29:47,060 --> 00:29:54,100
But if one day, you ever meet someone who can make your heart flutter,

312
00:29:56,020 --> 00:29:59,460
that person is someone you must cherish for life.

313
00:30:35,460 --> 00:30:36,780
After you, Boss.

314
00:30:38,360 --> 00:30:39,580
It’s okay, you first.

315
00:30:43,200 --> 00:30:46,420
If we keep being like this, will we get to talk then?

316
00:30:48,860 --> 00:30:49,960
Why are you still here?

317
00:30:50,930 --> 00:30:54,180
I already told Miss Preem that you can leave once you’re done.

318
00:30:54,530 --> 00:30:57,860
She already told me but I want to wait for you, Boss.

319
00:31:00,860 --> 00:31:02,560
Why do you think I’d return?

320
00:31:04,260 --> 00:31:06,220
Well, just a guess.

321
00:31:07,160 --> 00:31:11,930
I hadn’t been waiting long though. I was about to leave.

322
00:31:12,330 --> 00:31:14,780
You were just in time, Boss.

323
00:31:15,130 --> 00:31:16,580
Why do you want to talk to me?

324
00:31:16,580 --> 00:31:20,380
[Phone ringing]

325
00:31:21,730 --> 00:31:22,530
Please excuse me.

326
00:31:26,760 --> 00:31:27,560
Hello?

327
00:31:29,130 --> 00:31:31,100
Why are you whispering?

328
00:31:31,500 --> 00:31:33,420
That’s weird. Where are you now?

329
00:31:33,530 --> 00:31:39,460
I’m still at the hotel. Don’t worry, I’ll let you know when I’m home.

330
00:31:42,060 --> 00:31:43,100
Talk to you later.

331
00:31:49,060 --> 00:31:51,820
- I have something to…
- I have work to do.

332
00:31:54,130 --> 00:31:57,940
I can’t talk right now. You can wait if you want.

333
00:32:01,530 --> 00:32:06,100
But if someone’s waiting for you, you can just leave.

334
00:32:16,400 --> 00:32:17,940
Why suddenly moody?

335
00:32:18,500 --> 00:32:19,980
What’s wrong with her?

336
00:32:45,700 --> 00:32:51,360
I’m still at the hotel. Don’t worry, I’ll let you know when I’m home.

337
00:33:45,060 --> 00:33:47,140
You surely can sleep anywhere.

338
00:34:23,460 --> 00:34:30,179
If one day you ever meet someone who can make your heart flutter,

339
00:34:30,900 --> 00:34:34,580
that person is someone you must cherish for life.

340
00:35:08,660 --> 00:35:12,140
I’m sorry, Boss. I must have dozed off.

341
00:35:13,360 --> 00:35:16,930
A doze off? I’d say it was quite a deep sleep.

342
00:35:18,930 --> 00:35:20,600
Are you done with work, Boss?

343
00:35:21,700 --> 00:35:23,620
Mhm, I’m done.

344
00:35:24,530 --> 00:35:26,160
What is it that you want to talk to me about?

345
00:35:29,800 --> 00:35:31,100
Room service, sir.

346
00:35:38,100 --> 00:35:41,560
Well, I don’t know when you’ll finish working.

347
00:35:42,330 --> 00:35:46,020
And I still haven’t had dinner. Do you want to join me?

348
00:35:54,560 --> 00:35:57,860
I want to talk to you about Chef Ian’s menu.

349
00:35:59,260 --> 00:36:00,060
Go on then.

350
00:36:02,060 --> 00:36:05,340
It’s almost midnight. Maybe I shouldn’t eat it.

351
00:36:07,660 --> 00:36:09,500
But I had ordered for two.

352
00:36:09,530 --> 00:36:13,340
If you don’t eat it, how could I?

353
00:36:13,760 --> 00:36:16,740
Who would dare to eat while talking with the boss?

354
00:36:18,360 --> 00:36:21,340
Is there still anything you don’t dare to do?

355
00:36:22,960 --> 00:36:25,180
Please try this one, Boss.

356
00:36:25,180 --> 00:36:29,540
Fried Shrimp in Tamarind Sauce. It has dried chilli but not spicy at all.

357
00:36:30,380 --> 00:36:31,500
You go ahead.

358
00:36:32,740 --> 00:36:34,700
Are you afraid your shirt will get dirty?

359
00:36:36,100 --> 00:36:38,300
I can peel it for you.

360
00:36:38,560 --> 00:36:39,360
No need.

361
00:36:42,530 --> 00:36:43,560
I want to.

362
00:36:58,860 --> 00:37:02,380
You know, people usually do this thing to their lovers only.

363
00:37:03,060 --> 00:37:06,900
But since you’re the boss, I’ll give you an exemption this time.

364
00:37:10,700 --> 00:37:12,330
Why don’t you keep it for your lover then?

365
00:37:12,960 --> 00:37:15,180
I don’t have one yet.

366
00:37:15,820 --> 00:37:21,020
I’d rather spend my time taking care of you, in case you might want to give me more bonus.

367
00:37:28,360 --> 00:37:29,940
You’re still single?

368
00:37:34,700 --> 00:37:35,900
Why are you asking?

369
00:37:39,300 --> 00:37:40,740
Do you want to ask me out?

370
00:37:44,730 --> 00:37:45,700
I’m just kidding.

371
00:37:46,330 --> 00:37:48,380
Please don’t deduct my salary, Boss.

372
00:37:48,400 --> 00:37:50,660
I can barely make ends meet already.

373
00:38:29,460 --> 00:38:33,160
Are you showing off that you can do it better?

374
00:38:34,460 --> 00:38:36,580
I just don’t like owing to anybody.

375
00:38:54,060 --> 00:38:58,100
Do you know you always take everything in life so seriously

376
00:38:58,100 --> 00:39:00,700
Even with food.

377
00:39:03,800 --> 00:39:05,160
Does it make you uncomfortable?

378
00:39:15,200 --> 00:39:16,000
No,

379
00:39:16,700 --> 00:39:18,140
I find it challenging.

380
00:39:18,730 --> 00:39:21,730
It makes me want to see you break the rules even more.

381
00:39:24,360 --> 00:39:25,340
Not a chance.

382
00:39:26,330 --> 00:39:28,380
That makes it even more challenging.

383
00:39:31,200 --> 00:39:34,940
So, why do you want to talk to me? Is it about our project with Chef Ian?

384
00:39:37,260 --> 00:39:40,560
So…did you pick the Seafood Bucket menu?

385
00:39:43,900 --> 00:39:46,060
You think I stole your idea?

386
00:39:46,460 --> 00:39:47,660
Isn’t that true?

387
00:39:50,200 --> 00:39:51,940
I just chose what I think is appropriate.

388
00:39:55,960 --> 00:39:58,460
And I thought you liked my idea.

389
00:39:58,930 --> 00:40:03,300
I just want to hear you compliment me, like “Well done, Chonlada!”

390
00:40:04,260 --> 00:40:09,060
You’ve only been here a few weeks and still haven’t done anything much.

391
00:40:09,730 --> 00:40:13,540
It might be too fast to expect that kind of compliment.

392
00:40:14,960 --> 00:40:22,820
I know. Preem told me it took you almost a year to compliment her.

393
00:40:25,700 --> 00:40:29,180
But with you, it’ll probably take years.

394
00:40:33,330 --> 00:40:34,130
Just wait and see.

395
00:40:34,800 --> 00:40:38,460
I’ll make you say it yourself that I’m good at my job.

396
00:40:38,860 --> 00:40:42,380
And I’m sure I’ll take a shorter time than Preem.

397
00:41:16,330 --> 00:41:19,700
Good. I’ll be waiting.

398
00:41:22,400 --> 00:41:25,820
Good. I’ll be waiting.

399
00:41:48,100 --> 00:41:52,980
♫ Is this love? Is that what they call it?♫

400
00:41:52,980 --> 00:41:56,060
♫ When my heart starts to waver♫

401
00:41:56,060 --> 00:42:00,740
♫ Like a stream of water slowly pouring over my heart♫

402
00:42:00,740 --> 00:42:04,060
♫ From dusk till dawn, you’re never far from my thought♫

403
00:42:04,060 --> 00:42:08,500
♫Or is this love? Are you that someone...♫

404
00:42:08,500 --> 00:42:11,820
♫ ...who’s destined to be with me?♫

405
00:42:11,820 --> 00:42:18,020
♫ Is this really happening ? I really want to know ♫

406
00:42:18,020 --> 00:42:23,060
♫‘Cos you now hold a special place in my heart♫

407
00:42:28,300 --> 00:42:29,100
Thank you, Boss.

408
00:42:36,360 --> 00:42:37,600
Hold on, Chonlada.

409
00:42:43,760 --> 00:42:45,600
Have I done anything to upset you?

410
00:42:48,260 --> 00:42:50,820
Not at all. Why?

411
00:42:52,200 --> 00:42:55,460
You seem a bit quiet. You’ve been like this since we left the hotel.

412
00:43:00,930 --> 00:43:05,100
It’s probably because I ate so many prawns. What else could it be, Boss?

413
00:43:10,000 --> 00:43:11,460
Are you free this Sunday?

414
00:43:12,330 --> 00:43:13,860
This weekend? Yes.

415
00:43:15,960 --> 00:43:19,900
I have something to prepare for our project with Chef Ian.

416
00:43:20,530 --> 00:43:21,660
We’ll launch it in a few days.

417
00:43:23,300 --> 00:43:28,140
Miss Preem is still sick. Can you come with me instead?

418
00:43:34,560 --> 00:43:36,740
Don’t be silly, it’s not a date.

419
00:43:36,740 --> 00:43:40,580
She only wants me to help her pick the dress for Miss Preem.

420
00:43:40,580 --> 00:43:43,700
It’s just work. Nothing to fancy about.

421
00:43:46,500 --> 00:43:49,180
And I don’t think it’s anything special.

422
00:43:53,600 --> 00:43:58,260
Nate, I gotta go now. Yeah, talk to you later.

423
00:44:18,800 --> 00:44:19,900
Lada!

424
00:44:20,300 --> 00:44:21,100
Mum!

425
00:44:22,530 --> 00:44:24,740
Oh, I miss you so much.

426
00:44:30,560 --> 00:44:32,420
Why did you come home so late, sweetie?

427
00:44:32,420 --> 00:44:35,460
Your brother told me you got off work a while ago, didn’t you?

428
00:44:38,860 --> 00:44:41,000
You brought her here, Pat?

429
00:44:47,500 --> 00:44:49,660
You can go shower after you’re done unpacking, Mum.

430
00:44:49,800 --> 00:44:50,600
Okay.

431
00:45:05,860 --> 00:45:07,930
Did you bring her here to threaten me?

432
00:45:09,500 --> 00:45:11,020
Of course not, Lada.

433
00:45:11,930 --> 00:45:15,360
I went back to talk to Dad about the project during the low season.

434
00:45:16,330 --> 00:45:18,460
And then Miss Mon was asking about you.

435
00:45:19,360 --> 00:45:24,020
She seemed very worried so I decided to take her here to see you.

436
00:45:25,560 --> 00:45:29,020
I didn’t know Apo would come to drop you off this late.

437
00:45:29,900 --> 00:45:31,780
You’re lucky Miss Mon didn’t see her.

438
00:45:35,400 --> 00:45:36,660
Do you really not know?

439
00:45:40,060 --> 00:45:45,780
You think I brought your mother here on purpose so that she’d see you and Apo together?

440
00:45:46,060 --> 00:45:47,700
Why would I do that?

441
00:45:48,760 --> 00:45:51,500
Your mother knows you’re working for me.

442
00:45:53,800 --> 00:45:56,700
You already know Chef Ian’s going to work for Miss Apo, don’t you?

443
00:45:58,360 --> 00:46:01,660
Last time we met, you said you also didn’t know. How could I?

444
00:46:02,560 --> 00:46:05,780
You want to use me to ruin her project, don’t you?

445
00:46:11,960 --> 00:46:15,140
Add more lighting over here.

446
00:46:15,620 --> 00:46:17,980
And more plants too.

447
00:46:18,100 --> 00:46:20,580
I want more colourful flowers here.

448
00:46:20,660 --> 00:46:22,180
Send me the total budget once it’s done.

449
00:46:22,200 --> 00:46:23,000
Yes, Boss.

450
00:46:23,860 --> 00:46:25,000
I’ll leave it to you then, Miss Preem.

451
00:46:25,530 --> 00:46:26,360
Yes, Boss.

452
00:46:27,420 --> 00:46:29,100
- Let’s go.
- Yes.

453
00:46:36,660 --> 00:46:37,500
Chonlada.

454
00:46:40,600 --> 00:46:41,500
Miss Chonlada!

455
00:46:42,060 --> 00:46:44,740
Yes! Yes, Boss?

456
00:46:45,660 --> 00:46:46,940
Are you sure you’re awake?

457
00:46:47,730 --> 00:46:53,500
I…I was just listening to you giving orders to the staff.

458
00:46:56,360 --> 00:46:57,580
What did I say then?

459
00:47:00,540 --> 00:47:06,500
Well, you said you have to talk to the liaison officer and organiser…

460
00:47:06,500 --> 00:47:10,220
who are responsible for arranging the campaign with Chef Ian next week.

461
00:47:11,360 --> 00:47:12,980
I said that a while ago.

462
00:47:13,580 --> 00:47:17,340
You seem distracted today. Is there any problem?

463
00:47:19,200 --> 00:47:24,420
I’m sorry, Boss. It’s just that…this is my first big project.

464
00:47:24,740 --> 00:47:29,260
And I’m doing my best here but I’m still worried there might be any mistakes.

465
00:47:30,360 --> 00:47:31,600
Is that what you’re worried about?

466
00:47:34,860 --> 00:47:35,700
Yes.

467
00:47:38,930 --> 00:47:40,600
You can tell me if you have any problems.

468
00:47:41,660 --> 00:47:44,740
If you’re tired, you can take a break first.

469
00:47:48,900 --> 00:47:53,340
If I do that, I’m afraid I’d lose my chance to hear you compliment me then.

470
00:47:56,860 --> 00:47:58,330
I’ll work hard, Boss.

471
00:48:21,560 --> 00:48:22,900
Fah.

472
00:48:22,900 --> 00:48:26,860
Wow, the view from your office is amazing.

473
00:48:29,960 --> 00:48:31,180
How long have you been here?

474
00:48:31,760 --> 00:48:36,300
Long enough to see you giving orders to Miss Preem and Miss Chonlada.

475
00:48:41,560 --> 00:48:43,930
Is that what you want to talk to me about?

476
00:48:50,300 --> 00:48:55,530
Before the opening event, the hotel will provide Chef Ian with all the ingredients needed for her cooking show at the event.

477
00:48:55,700 --> 00:48:59,100
Chef Ian has already sent us the list of all ingredients she’d need.

478
00:48:59,500 --> 00:49:04,300
We’ll order them directly from the hotel’s food supplier for a freshness guarantee.

479
00:49:09,330 --> 00:49:11,940
Make sure you recheck everything in detail.

480
00:49:12,200 --> 00:49:14,980
This isn’t just an event to attract more customers,

481
00:49:15,330 --> 00:49:18,180
but also to create a first good impression for Chef Ian.

482
00:49:18,530 --> 00:49:21,660
So that she might agree to be our hotel chef in the future.

483
00:49:22,300 --> 00:49:24,620
Don’t make mistakes that might ruin the reputation,

484
00:49:24,620 --> 00:49:28,700
whether that of our hotel or of Chef Ian herself.

485
00:49:51,860 --> 00:49:54,360
Miss Preem, don’t forget to give me the minutes of meeting.

486
00:49:54,730 --> 00:49:56,400
And follow up on other things for me too.

487
00:49:57,060 --> 00:49:58,340
Yes, Boss.

488
00:50:01,130 --> 00:50:04,130
As for you, come with me.

489
00:50:11,460 --> 00:50:12,740
Where is she going?

490
00:50:17,260 --> 00:50:22,940
When you told me to help pick the outfit for the opening event, wasn't it supposed to be on Sunday?

491
00:50:24,100 --> 00:50:25,900
Sunday is your day off.

492
00:50:26,330 --> 00:50:27,900
I want you to get some rest.

493
00:50:29,730 --> 00:50:31,130
Please don’t worry about that, Boss.

494
00:50:31,530 --> 00:50:34,540
I’m willing to go all in if it’s about work.

495
00:50:35,500 --> 00:50:36,560
I know you are.

496
00:50:39,760 --> 00:50:42,020
But many people will come to the event.

497
00:50:43,000 --> 00:50:45,220
I just hope that after resting for a day before the event,

498
00:50:45,660 --> 00:50:49,260
you’ll be ready for hard work and won’t make any mistakes.

499
00:50:54,160 --> 00:50:58,140
Do you still want to hear me compliment you on your job, Chonlada?

500
00:51:03,560 --> 00:51:05,420
Your suit is ready, Miss Apo.

501
00:51:05,420 --> 00:51:06,300
Yes.

502
00:51:16,980 --> 00:51:17,900
Thank you.

503
00:51:21,660 --> 00:51:25,060
Help me decide which one is good for me.

504
00:51:37,330 --> 00:51:40,860
Actually, anything looks good on you.

505
00:51:41,300 --> 00:51:42,730
You don’t want to help me, do you?

506
00:51:43,800 --> 00:51:46,900
Of course, I do. It’s my job anyway.

507
00:51:49,260 --> 00:51:53,900
Does that mean if it weren’t, you wouldn’t want to do it?

508
00:51:59,360 --> 00:52:05,860
Do you know how I felt when I first took over from my father?

509
00:52:08,930 --> 00:52:11,460
Someone like you probably felt it was a piece of cake, didn’t you?

510
00:52:13,160 --> 00:52:14,780
Absolutely the other way round.

511
00:52:16,860 --> 00:52:21,400
I secretly cried in the toilet and my father still has no idea I did that.

512
00:52:24,330 --> 00:52:26,980
Are you kidding me, Boss?

513
00:52:30,330 --> 00:52:35,340
Apart from that, I also wanted to run somewhere far away.

514
00:52:38,560 --> 00:52:40,740
So that I’d be free from all the responsibilities.

515
00:52:44,360 --> 00:52:46,620
But when I came out of the toilet,

516
00:52:47,700 --> 00:52:53,020
I saw the maid mopping the floor that had a tiny stain on it.

517
00:52:54,600 --> 00:52:57,580
It was so tiny you wouldn't see it if you didn’t look closely.

518
00:52:59,360 --> 00:53:00,980
What I saw then…

519
00:53:03,200 --> 00:53:05,160
was a maid who dedicated herself in work…

520
00:53:06,600 --> 00:53:08,540
and did her best in her job…

521
00:53:09,500 --> 00:53:11,500
to help protect the Watin Group’s reputation.

522
00:53:16,200 --> 00:53:20,160
Then there I was, trying to run away.

523
00:53:32,560 --> 00:53:36,700
The Watin Group isn’t built by just a person or two.

524
00:53:38,700 --> 00:53:43,980
But by everyone who is willing to dedicate themselves.

525
00:53:46,100 --> 00:53:51,420
And when I said everyone, it also includes you, Chonlada.

526
00:53:55,700 --> 00:53:58,140
If you still see me as one of your team,

527
00:54:00,700 --> 00:54:02,160
you can always talk to me.

528
00:54:04,930 --> 00:54:06,130
I mightn’t be able to help much.

529
00:54:08,530 --> 00:54:10,580
But I’m a really good listener.

530
00:54:17,860 --> 00:54:23,180
Well, I…I saw that suit over there. I’ll go fetch it for you.

531
00:54:39,530 --> 00:54:42,730
You want to use me to ruin her project, don’t you?

532
00:54:44,600 --> 00:54:50,820
I wouldn’t say it like that. I actually still want that campaign opening with Chef Ian to happen.

533
00:54:53,000 --> 00:54:53,800
Then what?

534
00:54:55,060 --> 00:54:59,330
Then we make sure Chef Ian will never agree to work with the Watin Group again.

535
00:55:01,530 --> 00:55:02,500
You want me to…

536
00:55:02,660 --> 00:55:04,400
Sabotage Chef Ian’s food.

537
00:55:05,560 --> 00:55:08,180
And blame it all on the Watin Group.

538
00:55:10,860 --> 00:55:11,700
I won’t do it!

539
00:55:12,130 --> 00:55:14,930
Then you can pack your things and go home with Miss Mon.

540
00:55:17,400 --> 00:55:20,160
Because if she knows that you’re working as a mole at the Watin Group,

541
00:55:20,860 --> 00:55:22,500
she would never let you do it.

542
00:55:23,730 --> 00:55:29,140
But if you agree, this secret will remain as it is.

543
00:55:30,130 --> 00:55:35,940
And your mother will still be safe and won’t be dragged into this.

544
00:55:37,530 --> 00:55:40,130
You’ll also get to prove yourself to Dad.

545
00:56:11,530 --> 00:56:13,730
Is it so hard to decide, Chonlada?

546
00:56:19,330 --> 00:56:20,130
Yes?

547
00:56:25,340 --> 00:56:31,780
I’m just a little indecisive, Boss.

548
00:56:31,780 --> 00:56:39,940
Between these two, one isn’t the right colour for us but it’s preferred by someone else.

549
00:56:40,700 --> 00:56:47,860
While this one is the perfect colour for us but someone else mightn’t  like it.

550
00:56:49,020 --> 00:56:52,500
If it were you, would you choose being right or being preferred?

551
00:56:52,960 --> 00:56:53,760
Being right.

552
00:56:55,500 --> 00:56:58,060
You didn’t even stop to think at all.

553
00:56:58,600 --> 00:57:00,760
You didn’t even stop to think at all. Sometimes, preference also matters.

554
00:57:03,530 --> 00:57:08,940
I know. Sometimes, we have to live our life according to someone else’s preference.

555
00:57:09,360 --> 00:57:14,700
But if we insist on doing the right thing, even though it’s not to their likings;

556
00:57:15,930 --> 00:57:21,740
but if that person still has a sense of morals, they’ll understand us.

557
00:57:28,100 --> 00:57:33,140
Once you’ve decided, bring it out for me to try it.

558
00:58:10,300 --> 00:58:11,860
Welcome!

559
00:58:31,360 --> 00:58:32,600
Is everything all right?

560
00:58:33,380 --> 00:58:35,980
Hello, Mr. Adisorn.

561
00:58:55,130 --> 00:58:58,420
Can you please go and recheck if everything upfront is ready?

562
00:58:59,460 --> 00:59:00,460
Yes, Miss.

563
00:59:55,000 --> 00:59:55,780
[Next Episode]
Boss!

564
00:59:56,380 --> 00:59:58,100
It’s the guest who ate Chef Ian’s food.

565
00:59:58,460 --> 01:00:01,140
He suddenly threw up and got an upset stomach.

566
01:00:01,860 --> 01:00:03,660
Did someone poison the food?

567
01:00:04,020 --> 01:00:06,860
Do you have any idea who did it, Boss?

568
01:00:07,930 --> 01:00:09,220
Why would you want to know?

569
01:00:09,220 --> 01:00:10,540
Sis!

570
01:00:11,400 --> 01:00:13,260
- Fai.
- Miss you so much!

571
01:00:13,360 --> 01:00:14,700
This is Chonlada.

572
01:00:15,530 --> 01:00:18,060
Is she the girl Lom said is your girlfriend?

573
01:00:22,660 --> 01:00:23,860
Eat something first.

574
01:00:28,260 --> 01:00:29,060
Sis.

575
01:00:30,160 --> 01:00:32,380
This isn’t what you were wearing when you left home.

576
01:00:32,600 --> 01:00:34,380
They’re Chonlada’s.

